# scripts/.pii-denylist  —  copy this file to scripts/.pii-denylist (gitignored)
#
# The publish-safety gate (scripts/check-no-pii.mjs) loads scripts/.pii-denylist
# and FAILS the build if any term below appears in a public surface (git-tracked
# files or the npm publish tarball). Use it for the names the structural checks
# can't know about on their own: your real project, client, employer, and
# income-channel names — the kind of thing your task app is full of.
#
# Rules:
#   - one literal term per line, matched case-insensitively as a substring
#   - blank lines and #-comments are ignored
#   - this .example file ships; the real .pii-denylist never does (see .gitignore)
#
# The entries below are GENERIC PLACEHOLDERS to show the format. Replace them
# with your own real terms — and never commit the result.

# --- real project / codename examples (replace) ---
acme-rebrand
project-northstar

# --- real client / employer examples (replace) ---
globex-corp
initech

# --- income-channel / internal-label examples (replace) ---
consulting-retainer
course-revenue
